 :tx/rationale "GRAND UNIFICATION INSIGHT: P1 (coherence), P2 (tasks), P3 (telemetry), and P7 (task accuracy) are ALL instances of the same algebraic operation: extending observe_datom with a new commutative monoid accumulator. MaterializedViews already proves this pattern works for F(S) — it's a monoid homomorphism from (P(D), ∪) to (ℝ⁷, +). The same structure applies to: (1) ISP ENTITY SETS — live_projections collects BTreeSet<EntityId> per category. observe_datom already counts datoms but doesn't track entities. Add isp_intent_entities, isp_spec_entities, isp_impl_entities as HashSet<EntityId> to MaterializedViews. On each Assert, insert entity into appropriate set. Then check_coherence_fast reads from views.isp_* instead of scanning. Phi = |spec_entities - impl_covered_entities|. (2) TASK INDEX — maintain BTreeMap<EntityId, TaskStatus> in views. On :task/status Assert, update the map (LIVE semantics: latest-wins for same entity). Accurate counts = group-by on the map. Ready set = filter by deps. (3) TELEMETRY — fold session/spec/tx counters into observe_datom (4 counters, already have 2). (4) CONCEPT INDEX — maintain BTreeMap<EntityId, Vec<f32>> for concept centroids. On :concept/embedding Assert, update. concept assignment becomes O(concepts) not O(datoms). THE KEY ALGEBRAIC INVARIANT: For each accumulator A, the incremental path (fold observe_datom) must equal the batch path (scan all datoms). This is testable as a proptest: for ANY sequence of datoms, incremental == batch. This single invariant covers ALL accumulators simultaneously. DEPENDS-ON: The existing SOUND-ISO-v2 test already proves this for the fitness accumulator. Extend to ALL new accumulators."
